{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4212257f-3042-4cee-8003-d7d8672e36f9","content":"The issue is classic F# — **file compilation order matters**. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but it's listed *before* it in the `.fsproj`. F# requires dependencies to appear first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01RMCuckJFsgGWXHiMLZ6Faj","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-edad70375eba475086a52c425124e90e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-edad70375eba475086a52c425124e90e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"e222b3cf-2b67-4bf0-bdd6-89ac666d2211","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — depends on Domain.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain)\n2. Domain.fs — defines types\n3. Program.fs — depends on both\n\nServices.fs is listed before Domain.fs, but Services.fs uses types from Domain.fs. The fix is to reorder so Domain.fs comes first.\n\nCorrect order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"781D:2C79E8:11B54D:15B904:69F54A73"},"id":"a089748d-5562-4759-8b3f-0e25d5ff60ba","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:51:07.948Z","parentId":"c2da24ad-bd74-4580-9610-f9cbe017df9d"}
